Pre-heat your #oven{} to 180 degrees. Peel and chop @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into 2cm pieces) and finely chop the other half. Peel and finely chop the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and finely chopped) and roughly chop the @vine tomatoes{2}(roughly chopped into 3cm pieces) into 3cm pieces. Cut the @courgette{1}(cut in half lengthways, then halved again to create four strips and chopped into 2cm wide batons) in half lengthways, cut in half lengthways again to create four strips and then chop into batons about 2cm wide and the length of your index finger. Finely chop the @mint{1/2}(finely chopped). Pull the @oregano{3}(leaves pulled off stalks and finely chopped) off their stalks and finely chop.

Add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} to a #frying pan{} on a medium heat and add in your smaller chopped onion. Cook for ~{4%minutes} and then add your chopped garlic and cook for a further ~{1%minute}. Take off the heat.

Add the @lamb mince{250%g} to a #bowl{} with the @panko breadcrumbs{1}, half your chopped mint, your cooked onion and garlic mixture, a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{grind}. Mix together with your hands then shape your lamb mixture into balls (four per person).

Add the rest of your chopped onion along with your tomatoes and courgette to a deep #baking tray{}, drizzle over a glug of @oil{glug}, your chopped oregano, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{grind} and give everything a good shake. Add your meatballs to the tray as well and then put in your oven to cook for ~{25%minutes}.

In the meantime, bring a #pot{} of water to the boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch}. 10 mins before your veggies and meatballs are done, add the @orzo{3/4}(dried) to your boiling water and cook for ~{8-9%minutes} until your orzo is 'al dente'.

> 'Al dente' simply means that the orzo is cooked through but has a slight hint of firmness left in the middle.

When your orzo is cooked, remove the pot from the heat and drain.

When your veggies and meatballs are cooked, take them out of your oven. Add your drained orzo to the tray and stir through, then scatter your remaining mint and crumble the @feta cheese{1}(crumbled) over the top.

Serve in #bowls{} and enjoy!